WEBVTT

00:02.969 --> 00:06.138
Honey,
would you buy a closet called --

00:06.140 --> 00:09.308
shh! I am waiting to see
if I get to go tomorrow.

00:09.310 --> 00:11.276
Jury duty. You know,
you can just throw that away.

00:11.278 --> 00:13.112
There's no way they can
ever tell you got it.

00:13.114 --> 00:14.980
Jay,
you're a bad American.

00:14.982 --> 00:17.449
It is a privilege
to serve on a jury.

00:17.451 --> 00:20.285
For the first time,
I get to be part of it.

00:20.287 --> 00:22.721
Talk to me when you're eating a
tuna sandwich out of a machine.

00:22.723 --> 00:25.824
Anyway, it's a distressed-oak
model that I like to call --

00:25.826 --> 00:27.626
wait, wait!
Wait!

00:27.628 --> 00:29.194
Oh! I'm in!

00:29.196 --> 00:32.631
8:00 A.M. tomorrow.
Parking structure "c"!

00:32.633 --> 00:34.199
You're excited about
a parking structure?

00:34.201 --> 00:35.567
It's not even "a" or "b."

00:35.569 --> 00:38.670
You're gonna have to take my
place working at Joe's school.

00:38.672 --> 00:40.005
I can't do that.
I have a job.

00:40.007 --> 00:41.407
Have Claire cover
for you.

00:41.409 --> 00:43.909
She knows how to yell at people
and read the newspaper.

00:43.911 --> 00:45.577
What the hell's wrong
with that school?

00:45.579 --> 00:47.913
Aren't we paying them
so we don't have to
take care of our kid?

00:47.915 --> 00:50.249
That's not the way it works
at the learning barn.

00:50.251 --> 00:52.684
You know that they want
the parents to be involved

00:52.686 --> 00:54.486
so that they can bond
with the kids.

00:54.488 --> 00:56.255
What's wrong
with schools today?

00:56.257 --> 00:58.690
I'm successful,
and I had a nun with a mustache.

00:58.692 --> 01:00.526
Well, you better
get used to going there,

01:00.528 --> 01:02.394
because if I get put
into a murder trial,

01:02.396 --> 01:04.328
I could be gone for weeks.

01:04.331 --> 01:05.664
Maybe I should tell them

01:05.666 --> 01:07.699
that I have experience
on a firing squad.

01:07.701 --> 01:09.601
Why do you say crazy stuff
like that?

01:09.603 --> 01:11.170
Now, that isn't true,
is it?

01:11.172 --> 01:12.771
Wait a second.

01:12.773 --> 01:14.506
That new closet,
what did I say it was called?

01:14.508 --> 01:15.674
You never said.

01:15.676 --> 01:17.209
Damn it!

01:17.211 --> 01:19.511
That's why I need
a grease pencil in the shower.

01:19.513 --> 01:21.580
--<font color="#ffff00"> Captions by vitac</font> --

01:28.522 --> 01:30.189
♪♪

01:32.693 --> 01:34.259
<i> oh, I don't know, Haley.</i>

01:34.261 --> 01:37.930
<i> I mean, he is really cute and</i>
<i> really smart and really funny,</i>

01:37.932 --> 01:41.033
<i> but, oh, he's always</i>
<i> wearing clogs.</i>

01:41.035 --> 01:42.267
Oh, no, no.

01:42.269 --> 01:44.536
If he is not a chef, a nurse,
or a tulip salesman,

01:44.538 --> 01:45.804
you need to run.

01:45.806 --> 01:48.907
Hey, if your mother had that
attitude about a man in clogs,

01:48.909 --> 01:50.576
you two
wouldn't have a dad.

01:50.578 --> 01:52.778
Okay, thanks, dad.
I won't let you down.

01:52.780 --> 01:53.912
Bye.
[ Telephone beeps ]

01:53.914 --> 01:55.414
Guess what, guys.

01:55.416 --> 01:57.716
I am going to be the big boss
at work tomorrow,

01:57.718 --> 02:00.385
and coincidentally, it's
take your daughter to work day.

02:00.387 --> 02:02.254
Huh?
I'll go to work
with you, mom.

02:02.256 --> 02:04.256
Stop trying to get out
of community service.

02:04.258 --> 02:05.791
You need those hours
to graduate.

02:05.793 --> 02:07.092
And you're not
a daughter.

02:07.094 --> 02:08.259
Mom, dad, sit down.

02:08.262 --> 02:10.596
There's something
I need to talk to you about.

02:10.598 --> 02:11.463
You're going.

02:11.465 --> 02:13.098
So, girls,
what do you say?

02:13.100 --> 02:15.734
Uh, you know we're not 8,
and I have a job.

02:15.736 --> 02:18.103
You called in sick twice
last week because you had a zit.

02:18.105 --> 02:20.906
I work in fashion.
They told me not to come in.

02:20.908 --> 02:23.575
Alex, honey, your last class
tomorrow is at 10:00 A.M.,

02:23.577 --> 02:24.676
so if you hit the road --
<i> no, no, no, no!</i>

02:24.678 --> 02:25.777
<i> Haley, quick,</i>
<i> close the laptop!</i>

02:25.779 --> 02:27.946
Until now, I was always
a full-time mom,

02:27.948 --> 02:31.116
so the girls never had a chance
to see the other side of me --

02:31.118 --> 02:33.452
you know,
powerful woman in charge.

02:33.454 --> 02:35.821
Yeah, 'cause we never
get to see your tough side.

02:35.823 --> 02:37.122
[ Snorts ]

02:37.124 --> 02:38.857
[ Chuckles ]

02:38.859 --> 02:41.693
Come on, daddy, we're gonna
be late for your work.

02:41.695 --> 02:43.929
[ Whistle blows ]
I know.
I'm excited, too.

02:43.931 --> 02:45.364
[ Whistle blows ]
Okay, I was wrong.

02:45.366 --> 02:46.798
The whistles
aren't better outside.

02:46.800 --> 02:48.433
Are you sure you can
get all these groceries
home by yourself?

02:48.435 --> 02:50.102
I don't know.
I'm kind of scared.

02:50.104 --> 02:52.104
I've never
driven groceries home before.

02:52.106 --> 02:53.939
Hey, you guys.

02:53.941 --> 02:55.140
Ray-- Raymond?
Raymond!

02:55.142 --> 02:57.943
Hi.
Oh, it's been so long.

02:57.945 --> 03:01.180
Yeah. Haven't seen you since,
you know.

03:01.182 --> 03:02.781
Yeah.
Yeah.

03:02.783 --> 03:04.950
Raymond and j'Marcus
broke up three months ago,

03:04.952 --> 03:07.286
and they'd been together
almost as long as we have.

03:07.288 --> 03:08.987
J'Marcus
got all the friends,

03:08.989 --> 03:10.956
and Raymond
got all the confidence

03:10.958 --> 03:12.624
to go shopping
in his pajamas.

03:12.626 --> 03:13.859
You guys
having a party?

03:13.861 --> 03:15.794
No, no.
Party?
No, not a party.

03:15.796 --> 03:19.498
Olive medley, square napkins,
cracker trio.

03:19.500 --> 03:21.867
Um, well, these things
are just more for a --

03:21.869 --> 03:22.868
what would you say?

03:22.870 --> 03:24.069
Kind of like
a get-together.

03:24.071 --> 03:25.637
Get-together, get-together.
It's a last-minute thing.

03:25.639 --> 03:27.206
Yeah.
It's no big deal.

03:27.208 --> 03:28.874
Sounds fun.
No, it's not gonna be fun.

03:28.876 --> 03:29.808
No. It's crackers.

03:29.810 --> 03:31.009
Yeah.
It's supposed to rain.

03:31.011 --> 03:33.045
Well...
I'll see you guys.

03:33.047 --> 03:34.313
Yes.
You, too, Raymond.

03:34.315 --> 03:36.481
Bye-bye.
Take care of yourself.

03:36.483 --> 03:37.683
Phew!
That was close.

03:37.685 --> 03:39.518
I thought we were gonna
have to invite him.

03:39.520 --> 03:41.720
Hey, Raymond,
you should come tonight.

03:41.722 --> 03:42.888
Really?

03:42.890 --> 03:44.823
It wouldn't be a get-together
without Raymond.

03:44.825 --> 03:46.425
Right, cam?
Absolutely.

03:46.427 --> 03:48.894
Yeah.
Oh, you know what? But...

03:48.896 --> 03:51.730
I should tell you,
j'Marcus is gonna be there.
Yeah.

03:51.732 --> 03:53.265
So, if that's
gonna be uncomfortable,

03:53.267 --> 03:54.266
we totally understand.

03:54.268 --> 03:56.702
No, it's fine.
I'll be there.

03:56.704 --> 03:59.238
It'll be nice
to see j'Marcus again.

03:59.240 --> 04:01.740
Maybe he'll bring one
of those shirtless ab sluts

04:01.742 --> 04:03.475
I've seen
on his Facebook page.

04:04.411 --> 04:05.444
I'll see you guys.
Yeah. Yeah, see ya.

04:05.446 --> 04:06.712
Okay.
Look forward to it.

04:06.714 --> 04:08.213
-You, too.
-Yeah.
-Yeah.

04:08.215 --> 04:09.514
[ Whistle blows ]

04:09.516 --> 04:11.016
What was I
supposed to do?

04:11.018 --> 04:13.418
I mean, he was all sad
and pathetic and broken.

04:13.420 --> 04:16.555
Oh, well, yes, the perfect
addition to any party.

04:16.557 --> 04:18.089
They are gonna be
at each other's throats

04:18.091 --> 04:19.625
and ruin the whole night.
Come on, lily.

04:19.627 --> 04:20.759
Thanks to you,
we are throwing

04:20.761 --> 04:22.194
the antisocial event
of the season.

04:22.196 --> 04:24.062
Cam.
No, I'm late and I'd like
to leave on that.

04:24.064 --> 04:25.764
[ Sighs ]

04:25.766 --> 04:28.166
[ Indistinct conversations ]

04:28.936 --> 04:30.769
Hi.
I'm -- I'm here.

04:30.771 --> 04:33.438
Well,
this is a special treat.

04:33.440 --> 04:37.242
I spy with my little eye
a first-time volunteer!

04:37.244 --> 04:40.245
Gloria had jury duty, so no
chance I could get out of this

04:40.247 --> 04:41.913
by pretending
to be racist?

04:41.915 --> 04:44.583
[ Chuckles ] Anyway, uh...
What do you need?

04:44.585 --> 04:47.819
You can set up the paints,
make the kale smoothies,

04:47.821 --> 04:49.988
and wipe down
the rabbit hutch.

04:49.990 --> 04:51.657
On it.
Margaret?

04:51.659 --> 04:52.891
Paint, smoothies, hutch.

04:52.893 --> 04:54.259
Got it.
Excuse me.

04:54.261 --> 04:56.261
Who's this?
That's Margaret,
my assistant.

04:56.263 --> 04:58.263
I couldn't
have children.

04:58.265 --> 05:01.767
This is not how it works
with parent volunteers.

05:01.769 --> 05:03.068
You're already
playing fast and loose

05:03.070 --> 05:05.937
with that term "volunteer,"
so...What do you say?

05:05.939 --> 05:07.939
As much as we don't like
to use the word "no" --

05:07.941 --> 05:10.442
and, by the way, if any of these
little tykes start acting up,

05:10.444 --> 05:12.344
she's not afraid to get out
the wooden spoon.

05:12.346 --> 05:15.580
Jay, I know
it's a little scary,

05:15.582 --> 05:17.949
but you're going to
have to let her go.

05:17.951 --> 05:19.284
I don't want her to go.

05:19.286 --> 05:23.322
Margaret, just go.
I'll distract him.

05:23.324 --> 05:24.356
Come back.

05:24.358 --> 05:26.758
Margaret,
don't turn around.

05:29.596 --> 05:31.430
Okay, men.

05:31.432 --> 05:32.931
Gather 'round.

05:32.933 --> 05:35.100
Teachable moment.

05:35.102 --> 05:38.103
Don't think of community service
as a <i> requirement.</i>

05:38.105 --> 05:41.106
Think of cleaning up this park
as an <i> opportunity.</i>

05:41.108 --> 05:42.274
To get hepatitis?

05:42.276 --> 05:44.176
To make the world
a better place.

05:44.178 --> 05:45.344
That's why I'm here.

05:45.346 --> 05:47.279
I already did
my required hours.

05:47.281 --> 05:49.181
That's a fancy way
of saying you're a virgin.

05:49.183 --> 05:51.316
Joke all you want,
but this looks good

05:51.318 --> 05:55.454
on an application
to nyu or ucla or kfc.

05:55.456 --> 05:59.291
Okay, stop trash-talking
and start trash picking up.

05:59.293 --> 06:01.059
I-I'll get that.

06:01.061 --> 06:02.994
Hey!
There he is.

06:02.996 --> 06:04.730
Hey...You.

06:04.732 --> 06:06.798
How long's it been,
Mr. real estate?

06:06.800 --> 06:09.234
Well, you tell me,
Mr. you.

06:09.236 --> 06:11.737
I'm usually really good
with names and faces,

06:11.739 --> 06:14.072
but I could not remember
who this guy was.

06:14.074 --> 06:17.743
Fortunately, I found that
one perfectly worded question

06:17.745 --> 06:20.679
can get you
all the information you need.

06:20.681 --> 06:22.147
How's things?

06:22.149 --> 06:23.415
Good.
Uh-huh.

06:23.417 --> 06:25.217
How's the beautiful wife?

06:25.219 --> 06:26.585
Claire's great.
Yeah.

06:26.587 --> 06:28.420
Thank you so much
for asking.

06:28.422 --> 06:31.056
How's...
How's your situation?

06:31.058 --> 06:33.358
Oh, you know,
same ol', same ol'.
Mm-hmm.

06:33.360 --> 06:35.894
Actually, I'm glad
I'm running into you like this.

06:35.896 --> 06:37.062
My car just got towed,

06:37.064 --> 06:38.997
and my wallet and cellphone
were in there.

06:38.999 --> 06:42.834
Oh.
Could you possibly lend me
some money for cab fare or...

06:42.836 --> 06:44.169
Yes.
Oh.

06:44.171 --> 06:45.337
Of course.

06:45.339 --> 06:47.172
How's, uh,
$40 with a little extra

06:47.174 --> 06:48.774
in case you run
into trouble?

06:48.776 --> 06:51.877
I want to make sure you get back
to your house in, uh --

06:51.879 --> 06:52.944
time for dinner,
I hope.

06:52.946 --> 06:54.246
[ Both laugh ]

06:54.248 --> 06:55.747
Thanks, man.
You're the best.

06:55.749 --> 06:57.249
Hey, dad.

06:57.251 --> 06:58.250
Oh, my God.

06:58.252 --> 07:01.086
Last time I saw you,
you were so small.

07:01.088 --> 07:02.721
I better run.
Thanks, pal.

07:02.723 --> 07:05.190
All right, buddy.
Good to see you.

07:05.192 --> 07:06.591
Dad.
Hmm?

07:06.593 --> 07:07.926
That guy
just scammed you.

07:07.928 --> 07:09.261
No, he didn't.

07:09.263 --> 07:10.529
It's a classic scam.

07:10.531 --> 07:12.631
You pretend you know someone
and then borrow money.

07:12.633 --> 07:13.932
Okay.

07:13.934 --> 07:17.469
Men, gather 'round.
Teachable mome-- hey.

07:17.471 --> 07:21.406
Just -- a circle.
Gather means a circle.

07:21.408 --> 07:22.974
What did you just see?

07:22.976 --> 07:24.476
A squirrel
eating a band-aid.

07:24.478 --> 07:28.079
No. You saw a man helping out
a friend in need.

07:28.081 --> 07:30.382
If he was your friend,
what's his name?

07:30.384 --> 07:31.450
That slipped my mind.

07:31.452 --> 07:32.884
Did you recognize him
at all?

07:32.886 --> 07:34.753
Gentlemen,
don't be cynics like Luke.

07:34.755 --> 07:37.556
Don't let your skinny jeans cut
off the blood to your hearts.

07:37.558 --> 07:38.657
I'm with you, Phil.

07:38.659 --> 07:40.425
I choose to believe
in the goodness of men.

07:40.427 --> 07:42.060
You have a condom
stuck to your shoe.

07:42.062 --> 07:43.829
Oh.

07:44.765 --> 07:47.999
Defense also has no objection
to juror 14.

07:48.001 --> 07:50.101
Moving on, juror 15.

07:50.103 --> 07:53.171
Here. Ask me anything.
I am an American.

07:53.173 --> 07:54.139
All right.

07:54.141 --> 07:55.774
When someone
hires a lawyer,

07:55.776 --> 07:58.243
do you think they're more likely
to be guilty?

07:58.245 --> 07:59.177
No.

07:59.179 --> 08:00.612
Thank you.

08:00.614 --> 08:02.747
When they play with their hair
like he is,

08:02.749 --> 08:04.649
that's when I know
that they're guilty.

08:04.651 --> 08:08.019
Your honor, we request dismissal
of juror 15.

08:08.021 --> 08:09.688
Why?
I'm very good at reading people.

08:09.690 --> 08:10.989
He is guilty.

08:10.991 --> 08:14.125
And, by the way, so is the guy
that is behind him.

08:14.127 --> 08:15.427
He's not even on trial.

08:15.429 --> 08:16.761
Well, then he should be.

08:16.763 --> 08:18.597
I don't know what you did,
but you did it!

08:18.599 --> 08:19.431
Your honor.

08:19.433 --> 08:20.665
He's getting away.

08:20.667 --> 08:23.602
Juror 15,
you are dismissed.

08:23.604 --> 08:25.704
Ay! No, please,
your excellency.

08:25.706 --> 08:28.173
I just want to do my part
as a citizen.

08:28.175 --> 08:30.876
Lady, you can stop acting crazy.
You got out.

08:36.450 --> 08:37.616
Ladies, right this way.
Come on in.

08:37.618 --> 08:38.683
Oh, you're
in grandpa's office?

08:38.684 --> 08:40.018
Yeah.
Of course I am.

08:40.020 --> 08:42.320
It's no big deal.
I'm in here all the time.

08:42.322 --> 08:44.956
I mean, practically every day
at this...This point.

08:44.958 --> 08:46.291
This is...

08:46.293 --> 08:48.793
It's not usually
such a...Thing.

08:48.795 --> 08:50.195
There we go.
Have a seat.

08:50.197 --> 08:52.898
Does that guy with the tattoos
still work on the loading docks?

08:52.900 --> 08:54.866
When I was 15,
he gave me my first catcall.

08:54.868 --> 08:56.201
Pretty sure
that was his last day.

08:56.203 --> 08:57.202
Huh.
Hey.

08:57.204 --> 08:58.503
Oh, where's Jay?

08:58.505 --> 09:00.539
He's not here,
but I'm filling in.

09:00.541 --> 09:01.840
What can I do you for?

09:01.842 --> 09:03.208
I'll ask him tomorrow.

09:03.210 --> 09:04.509
Are you sure? Uh...

09:04.511 --> 09:09.247
Men are often intimidated
by a strong, powerful woman.

09:09.249 --> 09:10.715
Jay around?

09:10.717 --> 09:11.583
No, he's not.

09:11.585 --> 09:12.417
Oh, damn it.

09:12.419 --> 09:14.052
Hey, hey, hey, hey, hey.

09:14.054 --> 09:15.587
Captain's chair
is not empty.

09:15.589 --> 09:17.422
I'm here.
Let me help you.

09:17.424 --> 09:19.591
Seriously?
Seriously, huh?

09:19.593 --> 09:22.928
Okay. Well, we need to take a
delivery of 100 mirrored doors,

09:22.930 --> 09:25.263
but warehouse one and two
are both full.

09:25.265 --> 09:26.765
Huh.

09:26.767 --> 09:28.767
Okay, I know what to do.
I've got this. Uh...

09:28.769 --> 09:30.569
What if we move the drawers
into that busted semi

09:30.571 --> 09:31.937
in loading dock four?

09:31.939 --> 09:34.005
And that works because --
that frees up warehouse two.

09:34.007 --> 09:35.941
Worst-case scenario,
we're a day late on delivery.

09:35.943 --> 09:36.942
But they'll be mad at us.

09:36.944 --> 09:38.243
We'll give them a break
off shipping?

09:38.245 --> 09:39.244
I don't know.
Maybe like --

09:39.246 --> 09:40.545
10%! Ha.

09:40.547 --> 09:42.380
We did it.
Yeah!

09:42.382 --> 09:44.683
Huh?
[ Chuckles ]

09:44.685 --> 09:46.384
Good job, team.

09:46.386 --> 09:47.919
You see,
what I did there

09:47.921 --> 09:50.355
is I created a framework
for problem solving,

09:50.357 --> 09:52.591
and I didn't spoon-feed them
the answers.

09:52.593 --> 09:54.259
It's just
good management.

09:54.261 --> 09:57.062
Yeah. That's exactly
what it looked like.

09:57.064 --> 10:00.732
Hey, Jay, I need a decision
on that -- oh, boy.

10:00.734 --> 10:02.400
Get back here, dom.

10:02.402 --> 10:04.536
What needs
to be decided?

10:04.538 --> 10:07.372
Well, we're throwing that party
later for herm's retirement,

10:07.374 --> 10:09.074
and Jay's just
sort of the master

10:09.076 --> 10:10.875
when it comes
to picking out cakes.

10:10.877 --> 10:12.978
Oh, I'm here.
I can pick out a cake.

10:12.980 --> 10:14.279
Uh, ice cream cake.

10:14.281 --> 10:15.413
Mm, I don't know
about that.

10:15.415 --> 10:16.982
It's a cake.
It'll be fine.

10:16.984 --> 10:18.650
Okay, is there a number
where I could reach...
Just get it.

10:18.652 --> 10:20.318
...Jay?

10:20.320 --> 10:22.721
No matter how big or small
the issue,

10:22.723 --> 10:24.923
people want their leaders
to be decisive.

10:24.925 --> 10:27.058
Oh, definitely.
Of course.

10:27.060 --> 10:28.927
What flavor?
Mint chip.

10:28.929 --> 10:31.262
I'll come back.
I said mint chip!

10:31.264 --> 10:34.466
Hey, Joe!
You want to...

10:34.468 --> 10:37.102
I'm like Bruce Willis
in "the sixth sense."

10:37.104 --> 10:39.337
Jay, will you please
put the craft table

10:39.339 --> 10:40.505
over on the hemp rug?

10:40.507 --> 10:41.840
No.

10:41.842 --> 10:44.342
For a word you don't use,
I'm sure hearing it a lot.

10:44.344 --> 10:45.577
That's the craft table.

10:45.579 --> 10:47.445
You're holding
the feelings table,

10:47.447 --> 10:49.180
where we talk about
how we feel.

10:49.182 --> 10:53.952
Hey, Mr. table, I feel like
breaking you over a hippie.

10:53.954 --> 10:55.353
Well, you're the lawyer.

10:55.355 --> 10:57.422
When can I go
to jury duty again?

10:57.424 --> 10:58.957
Uh, you know,
I have no idea.

10:58.959 --> 11:01.426
You're literally the first
person who has ever asked that.

11:01.428 --> 11:02.661
I am so frustrated.

11:02.663 --> 11:05.630
This reminds me when I was
a little girl in my village

11:05.632 --> 11:06.765
and we had no power.

11:06.767 --> 11:08.299
Oh, this is the story
about the TV set

11:08.301 --> 11:09.601
powered by the donkey,
right?

11:09.603 --> 11:11.302
No, political power.

11:11.304 --> 11:13.772
We had no say
in anything.

11:13.774 --> 11:15.206
But now I am an American,

11:15.208 --> 11:17.842
so I thought things
were going to be different.

11:17.844 --> 11:20.845
I wanted to listen to testimony,
look at the evidence,

11:20.847 --> 11:24.549
have somebody burst in
with new information.

11:24.551 --> 11:26.384
Mitchell,
guess what just happened.

11:26.386 --> 11:27.786
You're home early.

11:27.788 --> 11:29.688
I have a two-hour lunch Monday,
Wednesday, and Friday.

11:29.690 --> 11:30.689
And summers off.

11:30.691 --> 11:32.624
I'm beginning to get
the low pay.

11:32.626 --> 11:33.692
This just in.

11:33.694 --> 11:35.493
Pepper says
he's not coming

11:35.495 --> 11:38.163
if both j'Marcus and Raymond
are here.

11:38.165 --> 11:40.632
"If I wanted this much tension
in a space that small,

11:40.634 --> 11:41.900
I'd go up
to my mother's room."

11:41.902 --> 11:43.068
That's not nice.

11:43.070 --> 11:45.570
We can't afford
to have another bad party.

11:45.572 --> 11:48.573
You have to call Raymond
right now and un-invite him.

11:48.575 --> 11:49.908
I-I can't believe
you and pepper

11:49.910 --> 11:51.242
aren't being more compassionate
about this.

11:51.244 --> 11:52.477
Raymond is a human being.

11:52.479 --> 11:56.081
What is the problem with
inviting majarcus and roland?

11:56.083 --> 11:57.315
They had
a horrible breakup.

11:57.317 --> 11:58.349
Months ago.

11:58.351 --> 12:00.585
Gloria,
what do you think?

12:00.587 --> 12:02.854
I think I need to know more
before I adjudicate.

12:02.856 --> 12:04.222
Adjudicate?

12:04.224 --> 12:07.592
When the skies were clear
and the donkey was very strong,

12:07.594 --> 12:10.862
we would watch
"L.A. law."

12:10.864 --> 12:13.898
That is the mockup room.

12:13.900 --> 12:15.366
Hey, guys.

12:15.368 --> 12:17.602
Keep up the mocking.
[ Chuckles ]

12:17.604 --> 12:19.671
It's important
to keep it fun.

12:19.673 --> 12:20.872
Ooh.
Look at that.

12:20.874 --> 12:22.741
The design team's
having a meeting.

12:22.743 --> 12:24.442
What do you say
we go in there

12:24.444 --> 12:26.411
and give them
a couple "attaboys," huh?

12:26.413 --> 12:28.246
No. No,
they look really busy.

12:28.248 --> 12:29.380
Don't be silly.

12:29.382 --> 12:32.183
Everybody wants face time
with the boss.

12:32.185 --> 12:33.518
Oh!

12:33.520 --> 12:34.886
[ Laughter ]

12:34.888 --> 12:35.620
Oh.

12:35.622 --> 12:36.855
Mom, are you okay?

12:36.857 --> 12:38.056
Alex, I'm fine.

12:38.058 --> 12:39.224
Oh, my God.
What?

12:39.226 --> 12:41.292
Your pupil
is the size of a nickel.
Oh.

12:41.294 --> 12:43.394
It looks like half of you
went to a rave.

12:43.396 --> 12:45.797
Claire, we have
a storage problem.

12:45.799 --> 12:48.099
If it's those mirrored doors,
I think I solved that one.

12:48.101 --> 12:50.702
No, some idiot ordered herm
an ice cream cake.

12:50.704 --> 12:52.537
I don't think
that name-calling --

12:52.539 --> 12:54.439
wait, how is that
a storage problem?

12:54.441 --> 12:55.974
The damn thing won't fit
in the freezer.

12:55.976 --> 12:57.442
It's melting
like a son of a bitch.

12:57.444 --> 13:00.478
Well, then, um, find
the smallest room we've got

13:00.480 --> 13:03.248
and crank the a/c
full blast, hmm?

13:03.250 --> 13:04.649
Oh, that's a great idea.
Thank you.

13:04.651 --> 13:06.918
Maybe later, we could turn
the heat up in the broom closet,

13:06.920 --> 13:07.919
bake muffins.

13:07.921 --> 13:09.387
Complete disaster.

13:09.389 --> 13:10.588
I'm gonna say something.

13:10.590 --> 13:12.624
You people
are being ridiculous.

13:12.626 --> 13:14.225
It's a freaking
mint chip cake.

13:14.227 --> 13:15.126
Mint chip?

13:15.128 --> 13:16.161
Yeah, mint chip.

13:16.163 --> 13:17.262
You're gonna love it.

13:17.264 --> 13:18.763
And if it's melting,
so what?

13:18.765 --> 13:20.398
We move the party up
a little.

13:20.400 --> 13:22.000
In fact,
why don't you tell everybody

13:22.002 --> 13:23.468
to be in the mill
in 10 minutes.

13:23.470 --> 13:24.669
But Jay's not here.

13:24.671 --> 13:26.137
Yeah, who will give
herm's farewell speech?

13:26.139 --> 13:27.505
I will.

13:27.507 --> 13:30.508
Give him the best farewell
speech herm has ever heard.

13:32.145 --> 13:33.845
Mom, are you sure
you're up for this?

13:33.847 --> 13:35.280
Yeah,
you look a little loopy.

13:35.282 --> 13:37.615
You know what?
I'll be fine.

13:37.617 --> 13:41.319
Just as soon as I figure out
who herm is.

13:42.322 --> 13:44.455
Keep it up, gentlemen.

13:44.457 --> 13:46.457
Hey, dad, remember that time
you were getting ripped off?

13:46.459 --> 13:47.759
You're still on this.

13:47.761 --> 13:49.694
I took a picture of the guy
and sent it to mom.

13:49.696 --> 13:51.830
She swears she's never
seen him before in her life.

13:51.832 --> 13:53.097
Your mom could say that

13:53.099 --> 13:55.099
about anyone she met at a party
with an open bar.

13:55.101 --> 13:57.936
Sounds like someone could use
another teachable moment.

13:57.938 --> 13:59.771
Oh, I'm good, dad.
Men, gather 'round.

13:59.773 --> 14:01.973
Teachable mo--
mother of...

14:01.975 --> 14:04.275
Luke here still thinks
I got ripped off,

14:04.277 --> 14:05.777
but if that guy wasn't legit,

14:05.779 --> 14:07.812
how did he know
that Luke was my son?

14:07.814 --> 14:09.047
Because
I called you dad.

14:09.049 --> 14:10.782
But how did he know
that you used to be small?

14:10.784 --> 14:12.116
I get the problem
with that one.

14:12.118 --> 14:14.853
Phil, don't give in
to his hipster cynicism.

14:14.855 --> 14:17.388
I admire your childlike faith
in people.

14:17.390 --> 14:19.057
And, Luke,
answer me this.

14:19.059 --> 14:20.892
If this guy
is such a con man,

14:20.894 --> 14:23.127
how did he know your dad
was Mr. real estate?

14:23.129 --> 14:24.229
Boom!

14:24.231 --> 14:26.531
Someone give this kid
a Mike to drop.

14:26.533 --> 14:27.799
Wow.
You got me.

14:27.801 --> 14:30.702
I'm actually feeling
a little dizzy because of that.

14:30.704 --> 14:32.570
My whole world view
has been rocked.

14:32.572 --> 14:35.073
I'm just gonna sit down
before I pass out.

14:37.911 --> 14:40.545
Pretty smug for a guy
sitting on pigeon droppings.

14:40.547 --> 14:42.046
Totally worth it.

14:48.388 --> 14:50.054
Jay: I was standing outside
feeling sorry for myself.

14:50.056 --> 14:52.423
[ Tambourine rattling ]
Erica:
♪ Larry the lonely leopard ♪

14:52.425 --> 14:54.859
♪ couldn't change his spots ♪

14:54.861 --> 14:58.196
♪ but once he put his smile on ♪

14:58.198 --> 15:01.099
♪ look at all the friends
he's got ♪

15:01.101 --> 15:03.268
Jay: Then I realized <i> I</i> was
Larry the lonely leopard.

15:03.270 --> 15:05.937
I just needed
to put my smile on.

15:05.939 --> 15:08.706
That song works
on so many levels.

15:08.708 --> 15:09.574
Whoo!
[ Tambourine rattles ]

15:09.576 --> 15:12.043
Hi, gang.
I'm Joe's dad.

15:12.045 --> 15:13.745
Hey, uh,
anybody want to hear a story?

15:13.747 --> 15:16.714
That's a great idea, Jay!
Okay.

15:16.716 --> 15:19.617
This one's called
"the teeny tiny house."

15:19.619 --> 15:20.852
Ooh.

15:20.854 --> 15:22.687
"In a teeny tiny town...

15:22.689 --> 15:24.355
On a teeny tiny block

15:24.357 --> 15:28.059
stood a teeny tiny house
with a teeny tiny --"

15:28.061 --> 15:29.227
you're old.

15:29.229 --> 15:31.429
You seen my wife, big ears?

15:31.431 --> 15:34.632
After that,
big ears' parents and I

15:34.634 --> 15:37.435
had to spend a little time
at the feelings table.

15:37.437 --> 15:39.871
Let me see
if I'm understanding this.

15:39.873 --> 15:44.575
So, you have known radar longer,
but jemima is the fun one.

15:44.577 --> 15:47.779
Uh, yes, and kudos for really
zeroing in on those names.

15:47.781 --> 15:49.647
Come on.
Raymond's fun.

15:49.649 --> 15:50.915
Name one fun thing
he does.

15:50.917 --> 15:52.583
[ Stammers ] One --
so many things.

15:52.585 --> 15:54.886
Okay, this [Laughs]
he does this thing

15:54.888 --> 15:56.754
where he imitates
his parents' answering machine.

15:56.756 --> 15:59.424
It's hilarious.
It kills every time.

15:59.426 --> 16:00.992
And it's j'Marcus.
Damn it.

16:00.994 --> 16:04.963
Mitchell, why is this Raymond
so important to you?

16:04.965 --> 16:06.631
What is it
that you're not telling us?

16:06.633 --> 16:07.832
Nothing.

16:07.834 --> 16:10.001
Isn't it true that
you have feelings for him?

16:10.003 --> 16:10.969
No.

16:10.971 --> 16:12.603
Admit it.
You have a crush on him.

16:12.605 --> 16:13.604
I don't.

16:13.606 --> 16:15.840
You love him.
You want to be with him.

16:15.842 --> 16:19.444
And you won't stop until
Cameron is out of the picture.

16:19.446 --> 16:21.112
Okay, okay,
you're -- you're crazy.

16:21.114 --> 16:23.114
Then why?
Be-- [ Sighs ]

16:23.116 --> 16:24.315
Because I <i> am</i> Raymond.

16:24.317 --> 16:25.149
Mm.

16:25.151 --> 16:26.417
What?

16:26.419 --> 16:28.486
Yeah,
if -- if we ever broke up,

16:28.488 --> 16:29.587
all of our friends
would pick you,

16:29.589 --> 16:30.922
and I'd be the one
who's left behind.

16:30.924 --> 16:33.324
Oh, honey,
that's not true.

16:33.326 --> 16:35.126
I would make them
invite you to stuff.

16:35.128 --> 16:37.929
He's lying. I can tell from the
way he's playing with his hair.

16:37.931 --> 16:39.497
No, I-I think
you really got to it.

16:39.499 --> 16:41.199
Say it.
Okay, fine -- cam!

16:41.201 --> 16:43.301
Cam's the one, all right?
Cam's the one I'm worried about.

16:43.303 --> 16:44.635
He's the one
who's gonna be left behind.

16:44.637 --> 16:46.604
I rest my case.

16:46.606 --> 16:48.272
Well,
I don't rest <i> mine.</i>

16:48.274 --> 16:50.208
Why do you think <i> I'm</i> the one
that's gonna be left behind?

16:50.210 --> 16:51.275
I'm the belle of the ball.

16:51.277 --> 16:52.810
Right there --
that's the type of thing

16:52.812 --> 16:54.479
you should
let other people say.

16:54.481 --> 16:55.780
About a woman.

16:55.782 --> 16:57.682
Nobody really cares about
your political rants.

16:57.684 --> 16:59.851
Our friends don't want to hear
about the koch brothers

16:59.853 --> 17:01.486
unless you're talking about
a couple hot guys

17:01.488 --> 17:02.620
in a bathroom
at a nightclub.

17:02.622 --> 17:03.788
Cam, you have no filter.

17:03.790 --> 17:05.490
You say whatever rude thing
you're thinking,

17:05.492 --> 17:06.723
and that
ruffles feathers.

17:06.726 --> 17:08.459
Feathers has
terrible breath,

17:08.461 --> 17:10.895
and I was the only one
with the decency to tell him.

17:10.896 --> 17:13.297
Okay, that's it.
Both of you sit down.

17:13.299 --> 17:14.632
I have
reached my decision.

17:14.634 --> 17:16.334
Raymond is coming
to the party.

17:16.336 --> 17:17.300
Yes!

17:17.303 --> 17:18.903
It's a smart precedent
to set,

17:18.905 --> 17:20.972
because after what
I heard here today,

17:20.973 --> 17:22.406
I think
there is a big chance

17:22.409 --> 17:24.976
that both of you
are going to be left out.

17:24.978 --> 17:27.545
Wow.
Uh, you know you're not
under oath, right?

17:30.083 --> 17:31.916
Monty:
Hey, there he is.

17:31.918 --> 17:33.151
[ Laughs ]

17:33.153 --> 17:34.986
How long's it been,
Mr. sport coat?

17:36.389 --> 17:40.058
And there it was.
The ultimate teachable moment.

17:42.262 --> 17:43.761
I guess
the answer is nothing.

17:43.763 --> 17:45.596
Nothing separates us
from animals.

17:45.598 --> 17:47.999
Grow up, Manny. Human beings
are basically terrible.

17:48.001 --> 17:48.833
Yeah.

17:48.835 --> 17:50.902
Hey!
What the hell?

17:50.904 --> 17:53.337
There he is!
Mr. full-of-garbage.

17:53.339 --> 17:54.739
What are you doing?

17:54.741 --> 17:57.575
Payback for turning a bunch
of innocent kids into cynics

17:57.577 --> 18:00.044
by preying on my good nature
and pretending you know me!

18:00.046 --> 18:00.845
Yeah!

18:00.847 --> 18:03.581
Phil -- Dr. monty lemon.

18:03.583 --> 18:04.949
I delivered Luke.

18:04.951 --> 18:07.418
Dr. monty lemon was thinner,
had more hair,

18:07.420 --> 18:10.855
and was a good 15 years younger
than you -- oh.

18:10.857 --> 18:13.458
Oh, yeah.
You're in my baby photos.

18:13.460 --> 18:15.293
[ Garbage rustling ]

18:15.295 --> 18:17.095
[ Indistinct conversations ]

18:17.097 --> 18:19.597
Anybody wants cake,
grab a cup.

18:19.599 --> 18:20.531
I'll have some.

18:20.533 --> 18:21.899
It's mint chip.

18:21.901 --> 18:23.468
Oh.

18:24.471 --> 18:26.170
[ Door rattles ]

18:27.207 --> 18:28.473
Did it.

18:28.475 --> 18:31.442
I got herm's personnel file,
and I wrote a kickass speech.

18:31.444 --> 18:32.944
Your eye is turning
black and blue.

18:32.946 --> 18:34.812
Yeah, and -- and what happened
to your hand?

18:34.814 --> 18:36.080
Um, nothing.

18:36.082 --> 18:38.483
I just gashed it trying to get
into the filing cabinet.

18:38.485 --> 18:41.219
Nothing a stitch or two
at urgent care can't fix.

18:41.221 --> 18:44.222
Hey, uh, "boss,"
are we gonna do this?

18:44.224 --> 18:46.124
Oh, we're doing this.

18:46.126 --> 18:47.425
I know
it's been a tricky day,

18:47.427 --> 18:50.928
but I am so glad the two of you
are here to see this.

18:50.930 --> 18:53.798
Okay, everyone,
gather 'round.

18:53.800 --> 18:54.732
Just bring it in.

18:54.734 --> 18:56.968
Let me
get your attention here.

18:56.970 --> 18:58.569
Oh, oh!

18:58.571 --> 18:59.737
[ Crowd "oh"s ]
Mom!
Mom!

18:59.739 --> 19:01.973
Stupid ice cream cake.
[ Groans ]

19:01.975 --> 19:03.641
I'm okay.
Ooh. Oh, God.

19:03.643 --> 19:04.775
Mom, stay down.

19:04.777 --> 19:06.611
No.
I need this.

19:06.613 --> 19:09.614
I know you think you need
to impress us, but you don't.

19:09.616 --> 19:11.516
You've impressed us
our whole lives.

19:11.518 --> 19:13.151
Alex:
And especially today.

19:13.153 --> 19:14.919
Nobody but you could put up
with this much punishment

19:14.921 --> 19:15.820
and keep going.

19:15.822 --> 19:17.121
It means so much.

19:17.123 --> 19:21.025
It really does, but [Inhales]
I've got a job to do.

19:21.027 --> 19:22.026
And I'm gonna do it.

19:22.028 --> 19:23.861
[ Sighs ]

19:27.600 --> 19:29.767
[ Claire breathing heavily ]

19:29.769 --> 19:34.639
Herm is so many things
to so many people.

19:34.641 --> 19:38.276
To his three sons,
he is a role model.

19:38.278 --> 19:42.346
To his wife, Dolores,
he is a devoted husband.

19:42.348 --> 19:45.116
And to his six
rescue beagles, he --

19:45.118 --> 19:47.218
wrong herm.
What?

19:47.220 --> 19:49.620
You're talking about
herm Anderson.

19:49.622 --> 19:52.690
Herm Kowalski is the one
who's retiring today.

19:52.692 --> 19:53.558
There are two herms?

19:53.560 --> 19:56.627
Three.
Okay, I'm out.

19:56.629 --> 19:57.728
Ow.

19:57.730 --> 20:00.364
Jay?

20:00.366 --> 20:02.233
In here with the booze.

20:02.235 --> 20:05.002
Oh, ay.
How are you?

20:05.004 --> 20:05.970
Fine. Why?

20:05.972 --> 20:07.171
The school called,

20:07.173 --> 20:10.308
and they said that
a mean boy made fun of you.

20:10.310 --> 20:12.743
Shh! He can probably hear us
from here.

20:12.745 --> 20:14.312
Kid had ears
bigger than Stella's.

20:14.314 --> 20:16.013
Other than that,
how was it?

20:16.015 --> 20:18.015
Like me in the tube slide --
not a good fit.

20:18.017 --> 20:19.250
Just not my thing.

20:19.252 --> 20:22.019
And don't give me that business
about bonding,

20:22.021 --> 20:23.721
because Joe didn't even know
I was there.

20:23.723 --> 20:25.256
Well, if it makes you feel
any better,

20:25.258 --> 20:27.491
I got rejected
from jury duty,

20:27.493 --> 20:29.060
so you don't have to
go to school anymore.

20:29.062 --> 20:30.494
Joe: Mommy! Mommy!

20:30.496 --> 20:33.831
Hey!
[ Speaks Spanish ]

20:33.833 --> 20:35.032
[ Chuckles ]
Ay-yi-yi.

20:35.034 --> 20:36.901
How was your school day?

20:36.903 --> 20:39.503
Best day ever
'cause daddy was there.

20:39.505 --> 20:40.871
Really?

20:40.873 --> 20:43.574
Did you like daddy
being in school?

20:43.576 --> 20:45.943
He made snacks,
he read books,

20:45.945 --> 20:48.679
and now I call Tommy
"big ears."

20:48.681 --> 20:50.081
I'm glad that stuck.
[ Laughs ]

20:50.083 --> 20:51.882
That's so nice.

20:51.884 --> 20:54.785
Daddy, can you come back
tomorrow?

20:54.787 --> 20:57.288
Do you really want me
to come back tomorrow?

20:57.290 --> 20:58.122
Yeah.

20:58.124 --> 20:59.023
Huh.

20:59.025 --> 21:00.625
What do you know?

21:00.627 --> 21:01.692
I'm a hit.

21:06.766 --> 21:08.933
[ Birds chirping ]
Jay: Anyone there?

21:08.935 --> 21:11.269
Hey, little help?

21:11.271 --> 21:12.770
Hello?

21:12.772 --> 21:13.638
Tommy?

21:13.640 --> 21:14.772
Tommy.

21:14.774 --> 21:16.374
[ Chuckling ] Oh, hey.
I'm kind of stuck here.

21:16.376 --> 21:17.441
Could you go
get a grown-up?

21:17.443 --> 21:19.410
Sorry.
Can't hear you.

21:19.412 --> 21:20.778
Really?

21:20.780 --> 21:22.213
With those ears?

21:22.215 --> 21:23.781
I'm sorry,
that was uncalled for.

21:23.783 --> 21:26.050
What do you want, money?
I got money.

21:26.052 --> 21:27.785
Go ahead,
use the credit cards.

21:27.787 --> 21:29.620
You'll spend less
than my wife.
